The article is a declaration by NATO and the Government of the Islamic Republic of Afghanistan on an enduring partnership. It emphasizes the strategic importance of stability and prosperity in Afghanistan to the security of the North Atlantic region. The declaration reaffirms the long-term commitment of both parties to a sovereign, independent, democratic, secure, and stable Afghanistan. NATO intends to provide sustained practical support to Afghan security institutions while respecting Afghan sovereignty and leadership. The Government of Afghanistan commits to actively carrying out its security, governance, and development responsibilities, as well as being an enduring partner to NATO. The article also discusses the principles and purpose of the partnership, as well as the content and management of the cooperation program resulting from the declaration. The partnership will be reviewed at senior political level at intervals of no more than three years. Non-NATO nations participating in ISAF are encouraged to contribute to the activities resulting from the declaration, subject to joint approval.